## The Profit Maximizing Rule

If **MR > MC** then you should **produce more**

If **MR < MC** then you should **produce less**

When **MR = MC** then you have the **highest profits**

This is the rule that you will use to decide how much to produce and maximize profits

NOTE: This has a big assumption that the price has been kept constant, in the example at $8.00
